cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for detecting lexical semantic change over time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of skip-gram with negative sampling architecture, which is a popular deep learning technique, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of principled simulations to control for biases, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval and vector space alignment, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of temporal referencing to avoid noise, which could fall under cs.DL (Deep Learning).
